author: Special to the Courier
title: Viking golfers take second in Hutch
text: Viking golfers take second in Hutch Special to the Courier winfieldcourier.com | 0 comments The Winfield Girls Golf team traveled to Carey Park in Hutchinson Thursday for the Hutchinson Invitational and took second place. “It is a good tournament,” coach David Bertholf said. “ It has some of the top teams from 4A to 6A. “We were runner-up to Manhattan by six strokes, but we had some good performances.” Sophomore Sadie Revell won the closest to the pin contest. She stuck one about four feet from hole eight.
